st|[[Electro house]]|[[nu-disco]]|[[electroclash]]|[[funktronica]]}}\n| length     = {{duration|m=54|s=10}}\n| label      = {{hlist|[[Ed Banger Records|Ed Banger]]|[[Because Music|Because]]}}\n| producer   = Justice\n| prev_title = [[Access All Arenas]]\n| prev_year  = 2013\n| next_title = [[Woman Worldwide]]\n| next_year  = 2018\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Justice (band)|Justice]] studio album\n | type       = studio\n | prev_title = [[Audio, Video, Disco]]\n | prev_year  = 2011\n | title      = Woman\n | year       = 2016\n | next_title =\n | next_year  =\n}}{{Singles\n | name        = Woman\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[Safe and Sound (Justice song)|Safe and Sound]]\n | single1date = 13 July 2016\n | single2     = Randy\n | single2date = 14 September 2016<ref name=\"RA\">{{cite web|url=https://www.residentadvisor.net/news.aspx?id=36427 |title=RA News: Justice unveil new album, Woman |website=Residentadvisor.net |date= |accessdate=15 September 2016}}</ref>\n | single3     = Alakazam !\n | single3date = 21 October 2016\n | single4     = Fire (radio edit)\n | single4date = 18 November 2016\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Woman''''' is the third [[studio album]] by the French [[electronic music]] duo [[Justice (band)|Justice]], released on 18 November 2016 by [[Ed Banger Records]] and [[Because Music]].<ref name=\"HBF\">{{cite web|last=Rafter |first=Andrew |url=http://www.harderbloggerfaster.com/2016/09/justice-share-new-artwork-ahead-third-album/ |title=Justice share new album artwork ahead of third album |website=Harderbloggerfaster.com |date=13 September 2016 |accessdate=15 September 2016}}</ref> \n\n==Overview==\nFour [[single (music)|singles]] were issued from the LP which are \"[[Safe and Sound (Justice song)|Safe and Sound]]\", \"Randy\", \"Alakazam !\", and \"Fire\". [[Xavier de Rosnay]] described the album as being \"like if you're in the car with your best friend and your lover and your kids.\"<ref>https://www.residentadvisor.net/news.aspx?id=36427</ref><ref>http://www.factmag.com/2016/09/14/justice-new-album-woman-share-randy/ - [[Factmag]]</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n\n{{Album ratings\n|ADM = 6.8/10<ref>{{cite web |title=Woman by Justice reviews |url=http://www.anydecentmusic.com/review/8388/Justice-Woman.aspx |website=[[AnyDecentMusic?]] |accessdate=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n|rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n|rev1Score = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref name=Allmusic>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/woman-mw0002977366|title=Justice: Woman|author=Phares, Heather|publisher=[[Allmusic]]|website=allmusic.com}}</ref>\n|rev2 = ''[[Consequence of Sound]]''\n|rev2Score = B\u2013<ref>{{cite web|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2016/11/album-review-justice-woman/|title=Justice: Woman|date=November 17, 2016|author=Eustice, Kyle|publisher=[[Consequence of Sound]]|website=consequenceofsound.net}}</ref>\n|rev3 = ''[[DIY (magazine)|DIY]]''\n|rev3Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=DIY>{{cite web|url=http://diymag.com/2016/11/18/justice-woman-album-review|title=Justice: Woman|date=November 18, 2016|author=Wright, Danny|publisher=[[DIY (magazine)|DIY]]|website=diymag.com}}</ref>\n|rev4 = ''[[Exclaim!]]''\n|rev4Score = 9/10<ref>{{cite web|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/justice-woman|title=Justice: Woman|date=November 18, 2016|author= Przybyslawski, Corinne|publisher= [[Exclaim]]|website=exclaim.ca}}</ref>\n|rev5 = ''[[Mixmag]]''\n|rev6Score = 8/10<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mixmag.net/feature/december-2016-18-albums-you-need-to-hear-this-month|title=DECEMBER: 18 ALBUMS YOU NEED TO HEAR THIS MONTH|date=December 2, 2016|author=Mixmag staff|publisher=[[Mixmag]]|website=mixmag.net}}</ref>\n|rev7 = ''[[MusicOMH]]''\n|rev7Score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.musicomh.com/reviews/albums/justice-woman|title=Justice: Woman|date=November 30, 2016|author=Williams, James|publisher=[[MusicOMH]]|website=musicomh.com}}</ref>\n|rev8 = ''[[New Musical Express|NME]]''\n|rev8Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web|