raph.co.uk/history/12031649/Whatever-happened-to-the-Bermuda-Triangle.html|title=The Bermuda Triangle: Whatever became of the myth|work=Telegraph.co.uk|access-date=2017-05-20|language=en|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161231000538/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/history/12031649/Whatever-happened-to-the-Bermuda-Triangle.html|archivedate=2016-12-31}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Things Fall Apart]] ''|| [[Chinua Achebe]] || English || 1958 || 20 million<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/565351/things-fall-apart-by-chinua-achebe/9780385474542/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2017-06-01 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171019220047/https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/565351/things-fall-apart-by-chinua-achebe/9780385474542/ |archivedate=2017-10-19 }}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Animal Farm]] ''|| [[George Orwell]] || English || 1945 || 20 million<ref>[http://www.bbc.com/culture/story/20170508-how-the-pink-floyd-pig-was-a-sign-of-protest The Floating Pig That Became a Sign of Protest] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170516054624/http://www.bbc.com/culture/story/20170508-how-the-pink-floyd-pig-was-a-sign-of-protest |date=2017-05-16 }} [[BBC Online]] 2017</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Wolf Totem]]'' (\u72fc\u56fe\u817e) || [[Jiang Rong]] || Chinese || 2004 || 20 million<ref>[http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/afc7e59c-ee43-11dc-a5c1-0000779fd2ac.html The Financial Times] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080519011627/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/afc7e59c-ee43-11dc-a5c1-0000779fd2ac.html |date=2008-05-19 }} on ''Wolf Totem'': \"Since it first appeared in 2004, Jiang Rong\u2019s Wolf Totem has sold as many as 20 million copies.\" (15 March 2008)</ref>\n|-style=\"background-color:lavender;\"\n|''[[The Happy Hooker|The Happy Hooker: My Own Story]]'' || [[Xaviera Hollander]] || English || 1971 || 20 million<ref>[http://www.philly.com/inquirer/magazine/20080626_Philmadelphia.html The Philadelphia Inquirer] on ''The Happy Ho