-in-dukan-diet The Toronto Star] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121024150342/http://www.thestar.com/living/article/974396--royal-connection-drives-interest-in-dukan-diet |date=2012-10-24 }} on ''The Dukan Diet'': \"The book has sold 10 million copies worldwide, but didn\u2019t really make an impression on North America until [...]\" (18 April 2011)</ref>\n|-style=\"background-color:lavender;\"\n|''[[The Joy of Sex]]''||[[Alex Comfort]]|| English || 1972 ||10 million<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/magazine-15309357 BBC Magazine] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111026173635/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/magazine-15309357 |date=2011-10-26 }} on ''The Joy of Sex'': \"The Joy of Sex ended up selling more than 10 million copies around the world \u2013 more than five million in the United States alone, where it stayed in the New York Times best-seller list for a decade.\" (26 October 2011).</ref>\n|-style=\"background-color:lavender;\"\n|''[[The Gospel According to Peanuts]]''||[[Robert L. Short]]|| English || 1965 ||10 million<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nwfdailynews.com/articles/seller-21424-gospel-ago.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-10-29 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091113031623/http://www.nwfdailynews.com/articles/seller-21424-gospel-ago.html |archivedate=2009-11-13 }} on ''The Gospel according to Peanuts'': \"The Gospel according to Peanuts ended up selling more than 10 million copies around the world.\"</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Life of Pi]]''||[[Yann Martel]]|| English || 2001 ||10 million<ref>{{cite web |url=https://latimes.com/entertainment/movies/moviesnow/la-et-mn-life-of-pi-20130218,0,3559592.story |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-02-25 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130223080308/http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/moviesnow/la-et-mn-life-of-pi-20130218,0,3559592.story |archivedate=2013-02-23 }} on ''Life of Pi'': \"It was based on a popular novel by Yann Mar